	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 4th 4:37 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.21]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good ideas.&nbsp;&nbsp;Wish I would have rethought my skill points a little more from the beginning...  but what the hell.  I got 10 levels comin up quick and 50 skill points.  Probably put that 11 into pick locks and dump the rest into make poison.  I think I'll be ok.<br><br>For any lower lvl Rogues, concentrate on that hide/sneak.  Spam it when you're healing, and WORK THAT BIND WOUND.  Spam everything when you can, Sense Direction, Sense Traps, Disarm Traps (works even if none are around), Spam Instill Doubt on corpses and other PCs, and if you're bored, put on a crappy 1hs or a 1hb on and sit around a pre-formed group and start bashing on their mobs a bit.  It's nice to ask first, but it's doubtful you'll KS them doing 1-2 dam per hit.  I've done this a lot with my 1hs and now it's dandy.<br>&nbsp;<br>-----------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth &lt;Winter Wolves of Bane&gt; - The Nameless</td></tr>
